																		FAQ!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=224440&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227607" alt="AdminBright" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=224440)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;" >AdminBright</a></span> <span class="odate time_1235726291 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Feb 2009 09:18</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-398425">
									

<p><strong>Q:</strong> What's going on here?<br />
<strong>A:</strong> Simple really. This is one of those collaborative writing exercises. The goal is to prank the previous holder of 050 in a particularly clever manner. Anyone can add on, at any time.</p>
<p><strong>Q:</strong>Is there any sort of format to this?<br />
<strong>A:</strong>NOPE! Use what your best at. Log, interviews, story format, whatever you want, I'm easy.</p>
<p><strong>Q:</strong>Who decides if something is more clever then the previous post?<br />
<strong>A:</strong>Technically, you do. However, if enough people think something just isn't that clever, it may get over ruled. Don't be afraid to post something that isn't more clever, a lot of this is just to get the imagination going.</p>
<p><strong>Q:</strong>What shouldn't I do?<br />
<strong>A:</strong>No killing other researchers in a prank unless it's Bright. He does tend to die rather easily. Also: Please be clever. Locking someone in the room with SCP-682 has been done to death. Arranging it so someone wakes up in bed with Abel, with a hangover, a sore rear end, and Abel cuddling them warmly, well, that takes talent.</p>
<p>Any other questions? If not, go for it!</p>

							</div>

